rComments: A very open-minded and supportive professor who specializes in assessments. He is very knowledgeable in theories and research highlights, and may be probed to share more of his insights. Like most academics, he may be trapped by the meaning and definition of terms more than necessary.
sometimes seems speaking for himself. Surprises you with unusal questions on the exams unlike the questions on assignment. Not clear and may be biased in grading. yes he is cute but...

Had him for the online curriculum course and learned nothing.  He offered no guidance and was unavailable for questions. He marked very hard considering he never told us his expectations and used inappropriate assessment tools. This course was a disaster and I learned absolutely nothing. Very disappointing.
nice personality; easy assignment; fun class; fair exams; hot; what else would you want in such a class?
Who'd have thought a graduate level intro to statistics course could be so fun?  Fair exams, interesting classes, great (and relevant) statistics examples.  Plus -- he's smokin' hot!
